- id: RA-SIM-SUPPORT-FAMILY-METHOD-003
  name: Exact-threshold subfamilies are not monotone augmented redundancy families
  domain: framing
  papers:
  - II
  statement: 'The v0.7 simulator instantiation uses exact-threshold subfamilies: at threshold k of n, the family is the set of all k-subsets of a parent support cut. Each member shares the parent''s certification
    surface and has cardinality exactly k. This is structurally distinct from a monotone augmented redundancy family, which would (a) include cuts of varying sizes (monotone), (b) include alternative parent
    cuts with member-level independent certification (augmented), or (c) admit repair / replacement over time. v0.7 results — including the channel-conditional rescue (RA-SIM-SUPPORT-FAMILY-004) and the
    certification-channel amplification (RA-SIM-SUPPORT-FAMILY-005) — should not be transferred to monotone augmented redundancy without an explicit second canonical run on a family generator with those
    properties. RA claims about "support-family redundancy" should specify the family-construction operator.'
  nature_targets:
  - methodological discipline distinguishing family-construction operators
  - pre-condition for transferring v0.7 findings to alternative family types
