- id: RA-SIM-SUPPORT-FAMILY-METHOD-004
  name: Cross-threshold resilience comparisons require apples-to-apples metrics within width-stratified slices
  domain: framing
  papers:
  - II
  statement: When comparing single-cut versus support-family resilience across channels, do not compare strict_readiness_loss_rate (parent-cut fate) directly to family_readiness_loss_rate (family-survival
    fate); these metrics have structurally different denominator events when the family-construction operator excludes the parent cut (which it does for exact-threshold subfamilies at threshold < 1.0 and
    width >= 2). The proper diagnostic is family_readiness_loss_rate evaluated at multiple thresholds within a fixed (mode, severity, support_width) slice; this isolates the genuine family-construction
    effect from metric-definition artifacts. Similarly, family_rescue_rate as defined (strict_lost ∧ family_survives) is structurally blind to resilience in cohorts where strict_lost cannot be true; report
    family_loss curves separately when comparing cross-channel resilience.
  nature_targets:
  - metric design for cross-threshold and cross-channel resilience comparison
  - pre-condition for non-misleading reporting of support-family results
