- id: RA-SIM-NATIVE-COMPONENT-DECOUPLE-METHOD-001
  name: Do not overclaim component-specific attribution when overlap surfaces are confounded
  domain: framing
  papers:
  - II
  statement: >
    Native certificate-overlap component attribution must distinguish cleanly
    resolved component surfaces from joint proxy surfaces. A claim that a
    specific component (orientation, ledger, etc.) carries the rescue signal
    for a specific mode (orientation_degradation, ledger_failure, etc.) is
    valid only when (a) that component shows independent variation from the
    other components on the data, AND (b) the component-specific specificity
    margin exceeds the threshold used in the v1.1 audit. Where (a) fails,
    the proper formulation is "rescue is carried by a joint
    {component-bundle} proxy"; where (b) fails, the proper qualifier is
    "weak or tied specificity". Sequencing discipline - generate or derive
    a distinct orientation-link surface from native orientation witnesses
    BEFORE BDG-LLC formal anchoring; otherwise the formal layer would
    anchor a confounded proxy.
